President Joe Biden met virtually with G7 leaders to discuss their support for Ukraine and the ongoing situation in the Middle East. The leaders also talked about global challenges such as sustainable development, climate change, and AI. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy joined the meeting, and the G7 leaders reiterated their commitment to support Ukraine and outlined additional steps to help Ukraine in their fight for independence and territorial integrity. They also expressed regret that Hamas refused to release all of its women hostages and that military operations resumed in the Middle East. The leaders thanked each other for their support of Israel and their efforts to bring humanitarian aid to Gaza. They also condemned Houthi attacks on commercial vessels in the Red Sea and believe that Iran enabled these attacks. The G7 leaders showed their commitment to close cooperation and unity in responding to events around the world. President Biden thanked the current G7 leader, Prime Minister Kishida, and welcomed Italy's G7 Presidency next year under Prime Minister Meloni.